
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gcr-viewer` yek barnameh graphiki ast baraye didan va modiriat sertificate-ha va kalid-haye SSL/TLS dar GNOME Keyring. Be shoma komak mikonad ke sertificate-ha va kalid-haye khod ra be asani bebinid, ezafe konid, va pak konid. 

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-ha.
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh version barnameh.
    🔹 `gcr-viewer` --> 🔑 Baz kardan barnameh baraye didan sertificate-ha dar GUI.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gcr-viewer

    🔹 Baz kardan barnameh gcr-viewer baraye didan sertificate-ha va kalid-ha az tarigh graphiki.

    $ gcr-viewer --version

    🔹 Namayesh version barnameh.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gcr-viewer
    
    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, panjereye graphiki gcr-viewer baz mishavad ke shoma mitavanid sertificate-ha va kalid-haye khod ra bebinid va modiriat konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gcr-viewer` command is a graphical utility to view and manage certificates and SSL/TLS keys in the GNOME Keyring. It allows you to easily view, add, and delete certificates and keys.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Display help message and options.
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Display program version.
    🔹 `gcr-viewer` --> 🔑 Open the graphical certificate viewer.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gcr-viewer

    🔹 Open the gcr-viewer application to view certificates and keys through the graphical interface.

    $ gcr-viewer --version

    🔹 Display the program version.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gcr-viewer

    🔹 Running this command opens the gcr-viewer graphical window, where you can view and manage your certificates and keys.
